<span class="JsGRdQ">We analyzed online conversations around Diwali from the past week to identify key trends among well-wishes from Gen Z, Millennial, and Gen X users. Social media listening helps us better identify what different target groups might prefer.</span>

&nbsp;
<h4><strong><span class="JsGRdQ">GEN Z: </span><span class="JsGRdQ" style="color: #ff0000;">MUSIC</span></strong></h4>
&nbsp;
<p class="_04xlpA direction-ltr align-start para-style-body"><span class="JsGRdQ">Almost a third of mentions for "Diwali" came from users aged 18-24, 17.5% of whom are students. </span><span class="JsGRdQ">"#Festivemelody" and "#diwalisong" are trending within the Gen Z conversation, indicating that music is of particular importance to these users.</span></p>
&nbsp;
<h4><strong><span class="JsGRdQ">MILLENNIALS: </span><span class="JsGRdQ" style="color: #ff0000;">FAMILY</span></strong></h4>
&nbsp;
<p class="_04xlpA direction-ltr align-start para-style-body"><span class="JsGRdQ">Millennial mentions contribute to over 50% of all results. Our research revealed Family and Parenting are a top interest among this group. </span><span class="JsGRdQ">This is reflected on social media listening with both 'friends' and 'families' among key themes within the conversation, as many cite having celebrated with their nearest and dearest.</span></p>
&nbsp;
<h4><strong><span class="JsGRdQ">GEN X: </span><span class="JsGRdQ" style="color: #ff0000;">OPTIMISM</span></strong></h4>
&nbsp;
