<strong><span class="S1PPyQ">February 22nd is the</span> <span class="S1PPyQ">World Encephalitis Day. RILA GLOBAL CONSULTING analyzed online conversations around Encephalitis and uncovered interesting insights.</span> </strong>

World Encephalitis Day aims to raise awareness about encephalitis, a rare but serious inflammation of the brain. In addition, the day aims to educate people about the causes, symptoms, treatment, and prevention of encephalitis and to promote better understanding and support for people affected by the disease. On World Encephalitis Day, people are also encouraged to share their personal stories, experiences, and knowledge about encephalitis on social media using the hashtag #WorldEncephalitisDay. The Encephalitis Society also organizes events and activities to raise awareness about the disease, including educational seminars, fundraising events, and community outreach programs.

